Description:—
Colonies (if any) and live cells not observed. Valves linear and isopolar, 20–23 µm long, 2–3 µm wide; areolae 
7 in
10 µm (
Figs 40–43
). External appearance of areolae a shallow depression with one small opening in the bottom. Occluding bars across the areolae simple, undivided arches (
Fig. 43
). Single papillae present between most of the areolae (
Fig. 43
). No apical spine or protrusion; each apex with a pit, within which was presumably the rimoportula opening (
Figs 43, 44
); internally the rimoportulae slit transapical (
Fig. 44
). Internal valve surface smooth and perforated only by the line of foramina below each areola (
Fig. 44
).
